# Trivy allow-list — accepted CVE exceptions for the runtime image.
#
# Every entry MUST have:
#   1. The CVE identifier.
#   2. A one-line note: why it's accepted and the expected expiry/review date.
#   3. A maintainer sign-off line (git author) so provenance is visible.
#
# No unexplained suppressions. If a CVE can be fixed by bumping a package
# or a base digest, do that instead — Dependabot opens the PR for you.

# (Intentionally empty at v2.0.0 release — no accepted exceptions.)
